title: Tim Jaguar Dikerjain Motor Balap
tags: [none]
description: Tim jaguar menyita satu unit sepeda motor tanpa kelengkapan surat. Pemiliknya mengaku hanya untuk netes, namun tindakan tersebut dinilai membahayakan pengendara lain. Selain tidak membawa kelengkapan surat, pengendara motor balap tersebut juga tidak mengenakan helm. Saat motor hendak dibawa, petugas sempat kewalahan lantaran terus - terusan mogok tak tau apa penyebabnya. Tak jauh dari lokasi, tim jaguar melihat kerumunan terlihat ada yang salah paham. Namun saat diperiksa, seseorang yang diduga sebagai dalang keriibutan melarikan diri ke semak-semak.

title: Gracie Abrams - I miss you, Iâ€™m sorry (Lyric Video)
tags: Gracie|Abrams|miss|you|Iâ€™m|sorry|(Lyric|Video)|under|exclusive|license|Interscope|Records|Pop
description: Listen to I miss you, I'm sorry, out now: https://smarturl.it/ImissyouImsorry a note from gracie: hi everyone i know everything is scary and uncertain right now and i thought that maybe this wasnâ€™t the right time to release anything, but the truth is that writing and listening to music have always grounded me whenever i find myself feeling scared or anxious or excited or lost or in love or out of control. this kind of anxiety is different. none of us have lived through something like this before. and yet, gratefully and impossibly, music continues to bring me comfort and iâ€™m thinking that might be true for some of you too. i co-wrote this song with sarah aarons and i donâ€™t know if iâ€™ll ever get over it. sarah is a hero of mine and of so many others. sheâ€™s brilliant, sheâ€™s humble, she is so fucking talented. writing with her is an experience iâ€™ll carry with me for the rest of my life (i love you sarah). blake produced this song. i love him, obviously. this song wouldnâ€™t be the same without him. i hope you like this song but mostly i hope youâ€™re well and safe. in the midst of all this, iâ€™m so moved by everyone working on the frontlines of this crisis. last week i shared my admiration and support for save the children, a group doing life changing work for kids around the world. today it feels important to lift up the incredible women working to support victims of domestic violence. while some of us are grateful to be sheltering in place, others are in extreme danger. women and children who live with abusive partners need the services of local organizations like jenesse center and national resources like the national domestic violence hotline. if youâ€™re interested in learning more, please check them out. https://jenesse.org/https://www.thehotline.org/ i love you guys.be safe.
